</div>
</div>



<p>It doesn't always work, but it can generally very quickly gather a decent amount of relevant information together to help solve things. Often it just solves the issue.</p>

<h2>
  <a name="conclusion" href="#conclusion">
  </a>
  Conclusion
</h2>

<p>There are so many coding agent tools out there. You likely end up building your own too. It's fairly easy to do that. Coding agents like <a href="https://pi.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PI</a> are designed for that.</p>

<p>I've found Squad to be a nice example of interesting and useful patterns, particularly when using Copilot at work. It's easy to use, relatively efficient, and I've found it saves me a bit of time. It's been a good addition to the toolset.</p>


